fields.name: The Winston Theatre
fields.description:
The Winston Theatre, named after former Chancellor Winston Churchill, is the University of Bristol Students' Union's flagship venue, and the home of Bristol student theatre since 1965.

A traditional proscenium arch theatre with dressing rooms, flexible orchestra pit and apron stage, permanent cyclorama, winched lighting bars and versatile hemp bars. The theatre features 204 fixed saleable seats.

For technical specification please contact the Stage Technicians' Association

The theatre is sometimes available for private hire. See the Bristol SU Website for more information.

Accessibility

Two wheelchair spaces at rear of auditorium. Lift access to box office (1st Floor) and wheelchair spaces (2nd Floor). Building access via wheelchair ramp; one disabled parking space.

Assistance available from front-of-house staff. Please email tickets@uobtheatre.com in advance to let us know of any particular requirements which we will do our best to cater for.

fields.name: The Pegg Theatre
fields.description:
The Pegg Studio Theatre is a flexible black box studio space, sited on the first floor of the Students' Union. The 80 seater venue can host a wide variety of performances, from traditional setups to theatre in the round.

For technical specifications please contact the Stage Technicians' Association. The theatre is sometimes available for private hire - please contact the Bristol SU Events Team for more information.

fields.name: The Anson Rooms
fields.description:
The Anson Room, named after 18th Century Admiral George Anson, is a large multipurpose hall, used for touring gigs, special events and occasionally student performances

Features a large high stage, high ceiling, and adjoining bar. Seated capacity 500, standing 1150.

The Anson Room is available for private hire. See the Bristol SU Website for more information.

fields.name: Stage Technicians Association
fields.description:
A friendly, fun and FREE society for anyone who enjoys the "dark side" of theatre!

We design, rig and crew Union shows, so whether you're interested in stage management, lighting, sound or even carpentry; whether you have years' experience or none; we are the society for you! Find us always in the theatre...

fields.name: Dramsoc
fields.description:
Dramsoc is the University of Bristol's longest running, largest and most prestigious performing arts society. Committed to student theatre, our aim is to nurture talent, produce high quality productions and cultivate a welcoming and inclusive environment.

We offer a wide variety of activities for our members including shows, workshops, schemes and socials.

We put on an average of 6 shows a year inside the Student’s Union and at external venues. This means that there are a variety of spaces available to you as a Dramsoc member – from the huge Winston Theatre or Pegg Studio within the Union, to the reputable Tobacco Factory or the atmospheric Lost Horizons. We always look to expand the range of opportunities available to our members. From showcases to an assortment of workshops and socials, involvement with Dramsoc always guarantees a chance for something new and fun. Moving further afield, we also fund teams to go to the Edinburgh Fringe Festival every summer.

Everyone is welcome at the many auditions we run throughout the year and absolutely anyone can propose for a slot to put on anything of their choosing, securing the funding on offer. This means that no two shows are the same and that there is opportunity to get involved on whatever level you would like.

fields.name: Musical Theatre Bristol
fields.description:
Music Theatre Bristol is one of the university’s biggest performing arts societies. Every year we put on two shows in the 200-seater Winston Theatre. The first, Showcase, features extracts from six different musicals, and is the biggest show of the year with a cast of nearly 70 performers. Additionally, we produce full-length musicals, with our most recent productions including LEGALLY BLONDE, CHICAGO and RENT, as well as 48 Hour Musicals, themed cabarets throughout the year and we hope to send a team up to Edinburgh Fringe! We will be hosting a Newbies' Cabaret, providing opportunities for those new to MTB to try their hand at directing, choreographing, and producing, as well as performing alongside other freshers!

The shows we put on are proposed and voted for by our members, and we pride ourselves on having a great reputation within the performing arts scene. We have both auditioned and un-auditioned productions and initiatives, allowing anyone who loves musical theatre to build upon their performance skills, learn new songs and dances, and meet lots of people.

Whether you're a performer, musician, composer, or are interested in production, you can be sure of finding your feet in MTB.

fields.name: PantoSoc
fields.description:
Everyone is guaranteed a part! We perform several pantomimes a year, including our epic Christmas show and our Panto-in-a-day, all written by society members.

If you want to get involved in Bristol's friendliest society, whether it's on stage, backstage or enjoying crazy socials, then this is the place for you!

fields.name: Spotlights
fields.description: Spotlights specialises in taking risks, finding challenges and discovering new talent. Whether you enjoy writing, directing, performing or the process of devising a piece of theatre, Spotlights is here to encourage, and make sure that you are able to create whatever the vision is that you have in your mind!

fields.name: BOpS
fields.description: Bristol University Operatic Society provides unmissable opportunities for students to discover the world of opera! We produce three full-scale operas each year: an annual production in term two, and two smaller works in term one as part of our annual opera festival, BOpSFest. This offers our talented members the opportunity to showcase smaller scale works and take part in outreach and enrichment activities. We also put on a show or concert during third term, to celebrate the end of the BOpS year. We are always on the lookout for singers, instrumentalists, conductors and directors.

fields.name: Dance Society
fields.description:
If you want to learn how to dance, try a new style, or continue honing your skills, dance society is for you. We run professionally taught classes in over 10 different styles and welcome all levels. The society holds an annual dance show, charity workshops as well as a variety of great social events! If you’re interested in a more competitive option, we also have competition teams which compete around the country!

UoB Dance Society offers members a full weekly time-table of professionally-led dance classes for all interests and abilities. The society holds a massive annual dance show, additional to smaller performances and competition opportunities. UoB Dance Society enjoys an enthusiastic atmosphere encouraged by various socials arranged throughout the year.

fields.name: Bristol Improv
fields.description:
Bristol Improv are the University of Bristol’s improvised comedy society. We host shows, scratch nights, workshops and events featuring improv comedy with the aim to build a fun and exciting comedy community for students here at the University, with no previous experience required!

We're all about improvisation; improvised comedy in particular - running workshops to help give you the skills, and putting on shows to give you the thrills. If you love comedy, drama or spontaneity, we're the society for you!

fields.name: A Cappella
fields.description: University of Bristol A Cappella Society is one of the biggest, most active societies at the University of Bristol. With 9 different groups under our umbrella, there’s always something coming up, whether that be a show, a social or simply a pub trip.We cater to anyone who wants to sing a cappella – whether this is in a big chorus, in a 4 person quartet or anything in between! We’ll also provide anyone who wants to set up their own group the advice and resources that they’ll need to get going. We recently welcomed Rebound (our auditioned alumni group) into the society.

fields.name: Revunions
fields.description:
The South-West's Comedy Crèche. We write, direct and perform our own sketch comedy. If you fancy getting involved, come along to our weekly workshops and join us in creating brand new sketches. We do lots of shows and every year take two up to the Edinburgh Festival Fringe. We also host many scratch nights, giving budding non-sketch comedians the chance to perform with us as well, so whatever kind of comedy you're into, there's loads of opportunity to get involved. Become a member with the Bristol Revunions to be kept up to date with all of this and more.

Twitter: @BrisRevunions

fields.name: Legally Blonde
fields.description:
Music Theatre Bristol are bending and snapping our way to the Winston Theatre this February with the first of our main shows: Legally Blonde!

Based on the 2001 film, Legally Blonde tells the story of Elle Woods – a sorority girl who follows love all the way to Harvard Law only to achieve more than anyone thought she was capable of! With only five performances be sure to get your tickets fast to avoid disappointment!

fields.name: Present Laughter
fields.description: Present Laughter

fields.name: Snow White: The Panto
fields.description:
Snow White is having a crisis. 18 and single, she's basically a spinster! Her mum, the Evil Queen, isn't helping things, and won't let Snow be with her one true love... the Mad Hatter! But is the Hatter all that he seems? (Oh no he isn't!) Can the Seven Dwarves save the day? And did somebody just invent Pokémon?? Let our narrators Sherlock and Watson tell you this hilarious tale, filled with songs (that are, not gonna lie, absolute bangers) and good times coming out of our ears.

Featuring classic fairytale characters like the Huntsman and Goldilocks, as well as not-so-classic ones from Game of Thrones to Adventure Time. How d'ya like them apples?
